I think you are confusion the text feedback with the actual event on server. Look at that log again, you cast the spell simultaneously with him hitting you (and did not get interrupted by the way).<P>And Mez spells are 3 second casting time. even cut in half it is 1.5, so your feedback would be a 2 second interval. Your log looks like it took just that. the spell WAS cast faster than base.<P><BR>Let's analyze it....<P>[21:21:02] You prepare to quickcast your next spell.<BR>[21:21:02] You begin quickcasting a Cloud of Senility spell!<P>### Now you actually got the quick cast and the initial spell cast off in the same second. So count this as half a second toward the spell cast.<P>[21:21:02] Bone attacks you with his rapier!<BR>[21:21:02] You are hit for 172 damage.<P>### Ouch!<P>[21:21:04] You cast a Cloud of Senility Spell!<P>2 seconds after the initial casting you get the spell off. No interrupts, nothing. Now since the first portion has the QC action AND the spell cast itself, we can count the spell itself as 21:21:02.5. Here this woudl make this 1 and a half seconds later it goes off, or half of the base 3 second casting time.<P>[21:21:04] Bone resists the effect!<P>### This is what really hurt you, or this woudl have went an entirely different way.<P>[21:21:04] The spell fails to affect the MileFortGate1!<BR>[21:21:04] The spell fails to affect the MileFortGate2!<BR>[21:21:04] Bone attacks you with his rapier!<BR>[21:21:04] You are hit for 128 damage.<BR>[21:21:04] Captain was just killed by Bone!<BR>[21:21:04] Your Strength has increased.<BR>[21:21:04] Your shield fades.<BR>[21:21:04] You have died. Type /release to return to your last bind point.<P>####<P>So quick cast did indeed work as intended.<P>--------------------<P>i3ullseye<BR>"You're good, but me? I'm Magic!"<P>Rictus -Sorceror(DAOC)/Rictus(EQ)<BR>DAOC Sorceror team lead...
