This all makes sense, but I'd like to point out another reason why quickcast sucks. Instants. All the middies and hibbies have instants. You think you can mez a middie before a skald or a healer gets off an instant mez or stun? Or how bout a thane's insta nuke? As soon as you start making the motion to cast a spell, BOOOM, stunned, or mezzed or nuked. We can not effectively do crowd control in situations like this. We have nothing to stop them. Hell, even if you DO get that quickcast off and mez them, they'll mez or stun you WHILE they're mezzed, and while you're standing there they'll start insta nuking you while mezzed. The only chance we have for it is against pure melee's. But usually once they've started hitting us we're going to die. <BR>I'm really starting to lose faith.<P>--------------------<P>Daenn Mindspinner<BR>Sorcerer of Albion Palomides<BR>Retribution
